reviews.review_text:
Nice Board, Nice Show. Run Rudolph Run is fun for Christmas, egg nog, and for laying down the yule log, but the real treat here is the second set.  I've always loved Brokendown as the classic oncore to a sissling, blow-out end.  And it's position is out-of-place for me.  But this time, with UJB as another classic oncore (and one of my favorites), I did the unusual and placed it as the second set opener that leads into a beautiful Dark Star (You can hear a little bit of David Crosby's "If Only I Can Remember My Name" album.).  It's a really nice transition.  I also wanted a very different hour since I hear Sugar Mag all the time.  So this is how I did the second set -- Brokendown, Dark Star > Deal, Stars & Stripes, Lovelight > King Bee > Mannish Boy > Two Trains > Lovelight and UJB.  One thing's for sure, ain't nothing like it anywhere else.  It's 55:57 of pure pleasure!

Thanks Ramrod and thanks Charlie.
